{
  "text": ". Alternatively, the generally observed mosaic of oxic and anoxic microniches in bioturbated sediments [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] may have prevented TRIS formation due to small-scale Fe 2+ or TH 2 S limitation. In any case, the level of TRIS precipitation was 18% higher than observed in diffusion-controlled defaunated sediment (Fig. 10) , where no suboxic zone was observed and TRIS precipitation was limited by upwards diffusion of Fe 2+ , leading to increased TH 2 S oxidation with O 2 at the sediment -water interface.",
